This paper is about improving the robustness and scalability of spoken dialogue systems through multi-dimensional dialogue modelling. It involves statistical approaches, domain adaptation, and reinforcement learning, which are all relevant to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of machine learning techniques such as multi-agent reinforcement learning and the focus on transferable conversational skills suggest that this paper could also be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper's emphasis on user simulation and human dialogue suggests that it could also be classified under Sound (cs.SD) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
